                <fr:title text="Predicate">Predicate</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong>predicate</fr:strong></fr:em> on a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a <fr:link href="jms-00KF.xml" title="Function" addr="jms-00KF" type="local">function</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi  \colon  A\to  {\mathopen {}\left  [2\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to the two-element set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [2\right  ]\mathclose {}}={\mathopen {}\left \{0,1\right \}\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. We say that a predicate <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi ]]></fr:tex> <fr:em><fr:strong>holds</fr:strong></fr:em> of a given element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> when <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi {\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=1]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
