            <fr:title text="The comprehension of a predicate">The comprehension of a <fr:link href="jms-00LO.xml" title="Predicate" addr="jms-00LO" type="local">predicate</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi \colon  A\to  {\mathopen {}\left  [2\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-00LO.xml" title="Predicate" addr="jms-00LO" type="local">predicate</fr:link> on a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>. The <fr:em><fr:strong>comprehension</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi ]]></fr:tex> is defined to be the following subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [\phi \right  ]\mathclose {}}\subseteq  A]]></fr:tex> spanned by elements at which <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi ]]></fr:tex> holds, as specified below:</fr:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 {\mathopen {}\left  [\phi \right  ]\mathclose {}} = {\mathopen {}\left \{a\in  A\,\middle \vert \,\phi {\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=1\right \}\mathclose {}}
]]></fr:tex>
          </fr:mainmatter>
